headlines.description: — Kyle Kuzma scored 25 points, and the Washington Wizards overcame Bradley Beal's back issues to beat the Detroit Pistons 120-99 on Tuesday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Beal limited by back, but Wizards roll past Pistons 120-99

events.name: Dallas Mavericks at New Orleans Pelicans

headlines.description: — Trey Murphy III couldn't miss, Jose Alvarado set a fiery tone from the opening tip and eight Pelicans players scored more than 10 points apiece.
headlines.shortLinkText: Murphy leads under-manned Pelicans past Mavericks, 113-111

events.name: LA Clippers at Oklahoma City Thunder

headlines.description: — There was no celebration for the Oklahoma City Thunder after earning their first win of the season in four tries.
headlines.shortLinkText: Gilgeous-Alexander's 33 help OKC top short-handed Clippers

events.name: Golden State Warriors at Phoenix Suns

headlines.description: — The technical fouls were piling high in the third quarter. So was Devin Booker's point total and the Phoenix Suns' lead.
headlines.shortLinkText: Suns push past Warriors for 134-105 win, Thompson ejected
